==English==

===Adjective phrase===
'''[[how]] [[many]]'''
# What number.

====Usage note====
*Used with [[countable]] nouns only.  The form used with [[uncountable]] nouns is '''[[how much]]'''.

====Translations====
'''what number'''
{{top}}
*French: [[combien de]] ''m and f''
{{mid}}
*Italian: [[quanti]] ''m plural'', quante ''f plural''
*Latin: [[quot]]
*Spanish: [[cuantos]] ''m'', [[cuantas]] ''f''
{{bottom}}

===Adverbial phrase===
'''how many'''
# The number that.

====Usage notes====
*Used with [[countable]] nouns only.  The form used with [[uncountable]] nouns is '''[[how many]]'''.

====Translations====
'''the number that'''
{{top}}
*French: [[combien de]] ''m and f''
{{mid}}
*Italian: [[quanti]] ''m plural'', quante ''f plural''
{{bottom}}

